After dedicating years to my gym journey, l’ve gained invaluable insights. Let me share three of them:

1. Prior to commencing your upper body regimen, prioritize forearm and shoulder preparation through wrist rotations, gentle weight exercises (such as 5-10 lb front raises and lateral raises), or cable routines. This proactive approach significantly minimizes the risk of injuries.

2. Kick off your workout with a dynamic approach by engaging in two sets of an isolation exercise that corresponds to the targeted muscle group of the day. For instance, consider cable flies or butterfly movements on chest day, lat pull-downs on back day, and leg extensions/leg curls on leg day. This technique generates an initial pump, enhancing the muscle-mind connection and setting the stage for effective muscle building.

3. Ensure a strategic 2-3 minutes of rest between sets. This optimal rest period empowers you to lift heavier weights to your utmost potential, resulting in substantial strength gains.

-

Credit to @migue1_fitness for the knowledge 👊🏽
